♪ I can teach you everything
In a single night ♪

01:32.300 --> 01:36.096
♪ I can make you hungry
Get an appetite ♪

01:36.179 --> 01:40.058
♪ I can tell a story
That will make you cry ♪

01:40.141 --> 01:43.394
♪ But nobody ever seems
Too bad at night ♪

01:43.478 --> 01:47.148
♪ 'Cause this town's too small
For a girl like me ♪

01:47.232 --> 01:50.819
♪ For a girl like me
For a girl like me ♪

01:51.402 --> 01:54.531
♪ It feels like I'm a walking tragedy ♪

01:54.864 --> 01:58.576
♪ Walking tragedy
Walking tragedy ♪

02:01.079 --> 02:03.623
♪ But do you ever wonder ♪

02:04.791 --> 02:07.460
♪ About the kid wonder ♪

02:08.628 --> 02:11.089
You are a magnificent beast.

02:12.674 --> 02:15.135
♪ I'm the kid wonder ♪

02:15.927 --> 02:17.929
[electric toothbrush buzzes]

02:20.140 --> 02:22.142
[hums]

02:41.411 --> 02:43.413
[indistinct chatter on TV]

02:44.831 --> 02:46.833
Good morning, Sierra. How did you sleep?

02:47.041 --> 02:48.751
Dreamed my socks ate my feet again.

02:49.377 --> 02:52.505
"Dreams are the bright creatures
of poem and legend,

02:52.589 --> 02:55.175
who sport on Earth in the night season

02:55.592 --> 02:58.052
and melt away
in the first beam of the sun."

02:58.803 --> 03:00.096
Dickens. Too obvious.

03:02.807 --> 03:03.933
[Sierra] Oh, freezer.

03:04.434 --> 03:05.310
-Bye, honey.
-Bye.

03:05.393 --> 03:07.687
-Wait.
-You have toothpaste on your face.

03:07.770 --> 03:08.730
No, no. Okay.

03:08.813 --> 03:11.191
Won't you sell more books if you have
the one teenager

03:11.274 --> 03:14.360
-who doesn't obsess over her looks?
-I'll pretend I don't hear the insult.

03:14.736 --> 03:16.237
Wait. I have a seminar

03:16.321 --> 03:18.531
and I want to run my new mantra
by you, okay?

03:18.740 --> 03:20.909
Finding love. L-O-V-E.

03:21.701 --> 03:25.413
L: Leave your insecurities
in the bathroom mirror.

03:26.372 --> 03:30.293
-O: Open yourself up to rejection.
-That's beautiful.

03:30.752 --> 03:31.794
-Yeah?
-Yeah.

03:32.754 --> 03:35.798
O is for "open yourself up to the risk
of rejection."

03:35.882 --> 03:39.427
V, just slit my vein before I die of
E, embarrassment.

03:40.011 --> 03:42.513
Okay, it's too bad your parents are
over-supportive.

03:42.597 --> 03:43.806
Just this morning, my mom said

03:43.890 --> 03:45.433
that she was gonna adopt her next kid,

03:45.516 --> 03:48.061
so he doesn't have to be
such a crushing disappointment.

03:48.144 --> 03:49.771
Oh, my God! Kenny!

03:50.355 --> 03:51.189
Get it together!

03:52.815 --> 03:53.942
I've got to catch that.

03:54.025 --> 03:55.443
Did you fall out of a plane?

03:56.027 --> 03:57.028
Pathetic.

03:57.528 --> 03:58.738
I really don't like her.

03:58.821 --> 04:00.698
You know? Like, she just makes my--

04:02.200 --> 04:04.494
Okay, what's up with
America's Most Unwanted?

04:04.619 --> 04:05.495
-Hey!
-I had to...

04:05.662 --> 04:07.664
-Come on!
-Well just let me... okay.

04:07.747 --> 04:08.665
New car fund.

04:08.957 --> 04:10.875
I'm pimping myself the only way I can.

04:10.959 --> 04:12.961
Why is the new car fund so unsexy?

04:13.294 --> 04:16.089
Oh, my goodness, that is
a really nice chassis.

04:16.422 --> 04:18.716
-You know, I don't need this from you.
-Okay, I'm sorry.

04:18.800 --> 04:19.926
Dan!

04:20.176 --> 04:22.011
I wonder what life is like for rejects.

04:22.095 --> 04:24.347
Can you pimp me out too?
I want a picture like that.

04:31.729 --> 04:32.605
So sad.

04:34.941 --> 04:38.945
Last unit, we analyzed the finest poetry
ever written,

04:39.279 --> 04:42.240
at which most of you failed
so miserably

04:42.323 --> 04:44.993
you must have been using
the pages as rolling paper.

04:45.076 --> 04:46.160
[boy] Pages are too thick.

04:46.995 --> 04:48.997
[students murmur, chuckle]

04:49.122 --> 04:51.374
[teacher] Now, I want you
to focus on writing

04:51.457 --> 04:53.626
your own original poetry.

04:54.335 --> 04:57.714
You kids should be happy that
I'm giving you some place

04:57.797 --> 04:59.632
to channel all this teen angst.

04:59.716 --> 05:02.427
Most of you just...sweat feelings.

05:03.177 --> 05:06.639
Know that once you perform
your poetry in class,

05:06.806 --> 05:08.725
it will count as 10% of your grade.

05:09.684 --> 05:11.936
Maybe yours can be about
your trans experience.

05:12.020 --> 05:13.229
Super-topical.

05:13.313 --> 05:15.523
And you can write about
your horrible personality.

05:16.107 --> 05:17.567
You can't talk to her like that.

05:17.817 --> 05:19.652
-I'm telling--
-The principal? Great.

05:19.861 --> 05:21.904
Then we can discuss your innovative use

05:21.988 --> 05:23.573
of a birth control dispenser

05:23.656 --> 05:25.700
to hide the answers of yesterday's quiz.

05:26.284 --> 05:28.036
What? You thought I just assumed

05:28.119 --> 05:29.537
you were extra-fertile?

05:31.372 --> 05:32.248
Come on, Chrissy.

05:33.458 --> 05:35.710
-[bell rings]
-Okay, let's go, come on.

05:38.171 --> 05:39.005
Come on.

05:40.048 --> 05:41.799
You're always the last one out.

05:42.842 --> 05:45.428
Thank you, but I don't need you to fight
my battles for me.

05:45.511 --> 05:47.638
Believe me. Everyone knows that,

05:47.722 --> 05:49.390
I just really enjoy it.

05:50.183 --> 05:51.976
Sierra, your last paper...

05:52.393 --> 05:53.686
really wowed me.

05:54.145 --> 05:56.522
I just know your poetry
is going to outshine

05:56.606 --> 05:58.566
all the other poems in the class.

05:58.649 --> 05:59.650
It's in your blood.

06:01.235 --> 06:03.946
Is there may be something else
I could do for 10%?

06:04.489 --> 06:05.573
A video or...

06:05.865 --> 06:08.034
You're aware that this is
an English class, right?

06:08.785 --> 06:09.869
Is there a problem?

06:11.412 --> 06:12.747
Not one you can solve,

06:12.830 --> 06:14.374
but thank you for asking.

06:14.457 --> 06:16.459
[toilet flushes]

06:17.085 --> 06:17.960
[camera shutter snaps]

06:21.547 --> 06:22.965
Move it, Frodo.

06:23.341 --> 06:24.759
Before you break the mirror.

06:31.766 --> 06:32.642
[Sierra] Quasimodo.

06:33.559 --> 06:34.560
[faucet turns off]

06:43.945 --> 06:44.946
What did you say?

06:49.742 --> 06:51.369
Frodo is from Lord of the Rings.

06:52.328 --> 06:54.580
You're thinking of Quasimodo,
The Hunchback of Notre Dame.

06:55.123 --> 06:57.959
He's ridiculed for his appearance
and represents a stratified class.

06:58.960 --> 07:01.546
Not unlike the structure of our own
high school popularity.

07:02.171 --> 07:04.173
-[girls laugh]
-[camera shutter snaps]

07:08.428 --> 07:11.305
I meant looking at you makes me
want to gouge my eyes out.

07:12.849 --> 07:13.975
I knew what you meant.

07:23.317 --> 07:25.194
I'm sorry. I didn't see you there.

07:28.448 --> 07:29.740
[man] For the next two weeks,

07:29.824 --> 07:32.660
we will be learning about the basics
of cell reproduction.

07:33.327 --> 07:34.537
Mitosis.

07:34.745 --> 07:36.539
If you look in your microscopes,

07:36.622 --> 07:38.958
you will see the first stage
of cell division,

07:39.542 --> 07:40.626
in which the chromatin

07:40.918 --> 07:43.087
condenses itself into two

07:43.421 --> 07:45.840
rod-shaped structures called chromosomes.

07:47.383 --> 07:50.428
-Thanks for asking.
-I have to find a story for my vlog.

07:51.387 --> 07:52.930
If I don't get into any college,

07:53.014 --> 07:55.892
I can sell my vlog to Buzzfeed or Vice.

07:55.975 --> 07:57.602
Or you can bank on your straight As.

07:57.685 --> 07:59.270
What is this, the '90s?

07:59.353 --> 08:00.980
I've got to create Google 2.0

08:01.063 --> 08:04.233
or swim backstroke
while playing the violin at the Olympics.

08:04.817 --> 08:06.486
Or create a new species of cat

08:06.569 --> 08:09.155
while volunteering
in a third world country at the same time.

08:15.119 --> 08:16.704
So, you want to go to Stanford?

08:17.121 --> 08:20.625
Yes. I almost got a perfect score
on my SATs.

08:20.833 --> 08:21.751
Perfect?

08:21.959 --> 08:23.503
You've got a sense of humor.

08:23.586 --> 08:25.213
I am gonna write that down.

08:25.505 --> 08:26.380
Funny.

08:27.048 --> 08:29.133
Have you started a social media movement,

08:29.217 --> 08:30.843
something that inspired social change?

08:30.927 --> 08:31.844
No, ma'am.

08:33.095 --> 08:34.388
I tutor, though.

08:36.891 --> 08:37.975
What are you writing?

08:38.059 --> 08:40.728
So what are you?
Other than a legacy student?

08:40.811 --> 08:43.814
-Excuse me?
-What's your sell? "Sierra Burgess is..."?

08:45.691 --> 08:47.068
May I be frank with you?

08:47.193 --> 08:49.111
-What were you before?
-Sierra.

08:49.320 --> 08:50.613
You're a good student,

08:50.947 --> 08:52.949
but there is nothing special
on your resume--

08:53.032 --> 08:54.867
except for a famous father.

08:55.409 --> 08:56.285
Work that angle.

08:56.369 --> 08:58.037
You could co-write a book.

09:00.122 --> 09:01.624
[chattering]

09:01.707 --> 09:02.959
-What?
-What?

09:03.084 --> 09:04.126
"Hey."

09:04.460 --> 09:06.963
College guys like Spence don't have
time to waste words.

09:08.089 --> 09:09.423
He's totally sexy.

09:09.507 --> 09:12.009
Kinda seems like a serial killer to me.

09:12.260 --> 09:13.094
What?

09:13.469 --> 09:16.097
Stare alert. West Pass boys.

09:17.515 --> 09:19.267
Oh my God, wait, I think he's coming over.

09:21.477 --> 09:24.063
My God, it looks like he's gonna jizz
his pants before he gets here.

09:24.188 --> 09:25.565
That would be so sad.

09:25.648 --> 09:26.899
Pretend… don't look.

09:32.905 --> 09:33.739
Hi.

09:33.823 --> 09:35.825
I mean, hey.

09:36.492 --> 09:37.326
I'm Jamey.

09:37.410 --> 09:40.413
I totally just said "hi"
like a thousand times.

09:40.705 --> 09:41.747
-Hi.
-Hey.

09:41.831 --> 09:43.040
Veronica.

09:43.749 --> 09:44.875
I guess you want my number?

09:46.544 --> 09:48.129
Yeah. Just like that?

09:49.714 --> 09:50.631
Easy.

09:55.636 --> 09:57.054
-You got it?
-Yeah, no. Yeah.

09:57.555 --> 09:58.639
555...

09:59.557 --> 10:00.891
0147.

10:02.268 --> 10:03.603
-Wait, that's--
-[kick under table]

10:05.479 --> 10:06.355
Text me sometime.

10:07.023 --> 10:07.857
I will.

10:08.941 --> 10:09.775
Bye.

10:15.948 --> 10:17.199
Wait, what just happened?

10:18.659 --> 10:19.744
Oh, my God!

10:21.120 --> 10:23.414
-Whose number was that?
-Sierra Burgess'.

10:24.665 --> 10:27.335
-Wait, you're so bad.
-I know.

10:27.418 --> 10:28.461
Why did you do that?

10:28.544 --> 10:30.212
He's "flash your boobs in Cancun" hot.

10:30.296 --> 10:33.591
Chrissy, you flashed your tits
to our ancient taxi driver in Cancun...

10:34.216 --> 10:36.427
Okay, Juan Diego needed the tip.

10:36.886 --> 10:38.054
He has a family to support.

10:38.137 --> 10:38.971
Guys...

10:39.847 --> 10:41.182
you see his friends?

10:44.018 --> 10:45.811
Only losers hang out with losers.

10:48.939 --> 10:49.774
God.

10:54.070 --> 10:55.029
[phone dings]

11:14.965 --> 11:15.800
Who is this?

11:23.724 --> 11:24.684
Is this a test?

11:24.767 --> 11:26.769
[marching band music playing]

11:30.856 --> 11:31.816
Sierra.

11:32.441 --> 11:33.818
Sierra, pay attention.

11:34.985 --> 11:35.820
I met a guy.

11:37.321 --> 11:39.824
Okay, not met-met. We texted.

11:40.324 --> 11:41.200
All night.

11:42.910 --> 11:43.953
By mistake.

11:44.245 --> 11:46.205
He may or may not think
that I'm somebody else.

11:46.288 --> 11:47.206
[students] Go!

11:47.289 --> 11:48.374
Fight!

11:49.041 --> 11:51.669
Go, fight, go, fight, win!

11:52.211 --> 11:55.131
Okay, he definitely thinks
I'm someone else.

11:55.464 --> 11:57.216
Oh yeah, definitely roll with that.

11:57.299 --> 11:59.635
