19:31.753 --> 19:32.588
Okay.

19:32.963 --> 19:34.590
Do not be selfish with the good stuff.

19:34.673 --> 19:36.717
Let me see. We don't have secrets
between each other.

19:36.800 --> 19:38.802
-No! Go on.
-Just let me see.

19:39.511 --> 19:41.263
Is that your poem for Ms. T's class?

19:41.346 --> 19:43.348
No, okay. No, Dan!

19:43.432 --> 19:45.434
Hey, no! Dan, Dan!

19:45.601 --> 19:48.353
-Hey, give me that phone back.
-Oh, Jamey. This is good.

19:48.437 --> 19:50.314
-This is good.
-Dan! Stop it!

19:50.397 --> 19:52.149
-Okay, just give me the phone back.
-[whoosh]

19:54.526 --> 19:57.321
"I have something to admit."

19:59.531 --> 20:00.490
Maybe he's married?

20:02.034 --> 20:02.868
Don't think so.

20:03.869 --> 20:05.954
Or gay. That could be good.

20:06.997 --> 20:07.831
Hold on.

20:35.108 --> 20:36.944
Alright, stop, stop!

20:37.027 --> 20:38.237
I love you, but stop.

20:45.702 --> 20:47.496
-Oh, my God.
-Oh, shit!

20:48.497 --> 20:49.873
Like, Veronica, Veronica?

20:50.332 --> 20:52.167
That's what I have to live up to?

20:53.252 --> 20:56.046
I think that she might have been
the reason

20:56.129 --> 20:57.881
that we lost a few of those games.

20:57.965 --> 21:00.175
Dude, that's it. That's it.

21:00.259 --> 21:01.969
You really, you trying to get out?

21:02.052 --> 21:04.596
You trying to get out?
What you want, what you want, bro?

21:06.181 --> 21:07.516
Damn, okay.

21:07.808 --> 21:09.268
-Easy fix.
-What?

21:09.559 --> 21:10.644
Hey, hey.

21:10.727 --> 21:12.896
Listen, he gotta find out
the truth sometime.

21:12.980 --> 21:15.357
Stop it! I'll tell him myself, okay?

21:15.440 --> 21:17.859
You don't need to.
That's why you have a best friend like me.

21:18.068 --> 21:21.571
-"Dear white boy..." He does have abs.
-Dan! Dan, come on!

21:21.655 --> 21:23.907
Attaching a real photo.

21:24.366 --> 21:27.786
-Dan, Dan, Dan!
-What, what? Okay, okay!

21:27.869 --> 21:29.496
Sierra, Sierra, I'm sorry.

21:29.830 --> 21:30.706
I'm sorry.

21:33.333 --> 21:34.501
I didn't mean to push it.

21:38.380 --> 21:41.842
Theoretically, I can still make this work
until the big game when East plays West.

21:41.925 --> 21:43.135
When is that?

21:44.052 --> 21:46.888
I don't know, check the band schedule.
I think two weeks.

21:48.015 --> 21:49.016
Two weeks?

21:51.560 --> 21:55.981
Okay, well, obviously I can't have him
going up to Veronica then.

21:59.026 --> 22:00.986
-You think I'm crazy?
-Mm-hmm.

22:02.237 --> 22:04.323
Look, I'm not stupid, okay? I...

22:05.324 --> 22:09.328
I know that he's imagining her
when he's talking to me, but...

22:12.873 --> 22:14.291
they're my words.

22:15.292 --> 22:16.626
He's falling for me.

22:17.336 --> 22:20.964
And of all the billions of phone numbers
in the world, he texted mine.

22:21.423 --> 22:25.177
Now, doesn't that seem
like some type of cosmic sign?

22:26.386 --> 22:28.472
[Dan] That you're not the cheerleader
he's looking for?

22:29.598 --> 22:30.474
It's your turn.

22:30.932 --> 22:33.518
[Veronica] No, no, no.
He was fine yesterday.

22:33.602 --> 22:36.730
We went out yesterday and then
this morning, he just texted me.

22:37.898 --> 22:39.024
I don't understand.

22:39.107 --> 22:41.151
Even chromosomes can find their mates.

22:41.818 --> 22:44.321
Oh, yeah, metaphase looks like
a very hot-ass date.

22:44.404 --> 22:46.907
He said I'm not smart enough
for his college friends or whatever.

22:47.282 --> 22:50.452
You honestly should be with someone
who's more like you.

22:50.535 --> 22:52.829
I don't wanna be with someone
who's more like me.

22:53.163 --> 22:54.414
I want to be with Spence.

22:54.498 --> 22:56.833
Ladies! I'd hate for my class

22:56.917 --> 22:58.293
to interrupt your gab session,

22:58.377 --> 23:01.004
but save the theatrics for your
lunch break.

23:08.762 --> 23:09.596
[door slams]

23:10.764 --> 23:12.099
She was upset.

23:17.521 --> 23:19.648
I know that face.
That's the one that give me creeps.

23:19.731 --> 23:21.942
Don't do it, okay. Step off the ledge.

23:22.025 --> 23:24.152
Excuse me, may I go
to the bathroom, please?

23:39.501 --> 23:41.128
-[Veronica sniffles]
-It's flu season.

23:41.962 --> 23:43.672
You should really wipe that on your elbow.

23:44.423 --> 23:45.465
What do you want?

23:46.508 --> 23:49.219
I know you've been giving out my number
to random guys.

23:49.928 --> 23:51.388
Yeah, so?

23:51.471 --> 23:52.889
I think we can help each other.

23:54.641 --> 23:57.727
If you think I'm gonna host a pity party
for a reject like you,

23:57.811 --> 23:59.771
you've added crazy pills to your
hormone pills,

23:59.855 --> 24:01.523
when you really need diet pills.

24:04.067 --> 24:04.901
Are you done?

24:08.238 --> 24:09.072
Maybe.

24:09.239 --> 24:11.825
Good, because I can help you seem smarter.

24:11.908 --> 24:13.493
To get back that guy.

24:14.911 --> 24:17.038
-How?
-I tutor people all the time.

24:18.248 --> 24:20.292
But I do need one minor favor in return.

24:21.960 --> 24:23.462
No, psycho stalker.

24:23.545 --> 24:24.838
You can't be friends with me.

24:24.921 --> 24:26.673
You know how many people
beg to do my homework

24:26.756 --> 24:28.091
in exchange for me following them?

24:29.885 --> 24:31.136
Twenty thousand followers.

24:32.053 --> 24:33.054
Following zero.

24:33.638 --> 24:37.517
Yeah, that's really impressive,
but I don't want to be your friend,

24:37.601 --> 24:39.019
on social media or otherwise.

24:39.603 --> 24:40.437
Liar.

24:40.770 --> 24:43.940
-Everyone does.
-Yeah, not me. Sorry.

24:44.065 --> 24:45.400
I'll see you after school.

24:46.026 --> 24:46.943
Text me your address.

24:47.027 --> 24:48.445
You already have my number.

25:05.795 --> 25:06.713
What?

25:08.882 --> 25:10.300
I'm just gonna get my stuff.

25:11.676 --> 25:14.888
[man on TV] Now, now it kind of...
It blows my mind, okay?

25:15.096 --> 25:16.890
I'm tired and it blows my mind.

25:17.724 --> 25:20.644
[woman on TV] I see it coming out
pretty quickly. The stain is gone.

25:20.727 --> 25:22.938
Pick your jaw off the floor,
mouth breather.

25:23.146 --> 25:24.356
My room's upstairs.

25:26.691 --> 25:29.194
And don't put your man hands
on the railings.

25:29.778 --> 25:31.530
My mom hates fingerprints.

25:33.156 --> 25:34.658
Because she's a criminal?

25:43.333 --> 25:44.292
What are you doing?

25:45.126 --> 25:48.213
Hurry up, teach me your mind voodoo tricks
or whatever.

25:48.505 --> 25:51.007
-There are no tricks. We have to study.
-Study?

25:51.508 --> 25:53.009
-Yeah.
-What do I need you for?

25:53.093 --> 25:56.930
If I wanted to study I could
just open up a book and do it myself.

25:57.013 --> 26:00.225
I'm gonna teach you the right things
to study so you can impress Spence.

26:00.684 --> 26:02.519
-He's a college freshman, right?
-Yeah.

26:02.602 --> 26:03.603
Okay, cool.

26:04.229 --> 26:07.023
Well, then I am going to teach you
the basics.

26:07.107 --> 26:08.942
The stuff he's learning
in his 101 classes,

26:09.025 --> 26:11.319
-like Shakespeare and Nietzsche.
-[woman] Hello? Veronica?

26:11.778 --> 26:13.530
Better not tell anyone about this.

26:14.114 --> 26:15.365
I wasn't planning on it.

26:15.615 --> 26:16.741
[woman] Veronica?

26:17.701 --> 26:19.828
Veronica, what are you doing home?

26:20.036 --> 26:21.746
Why aren't you in practice?

26:21.830 --> 26:23.290
Did they cut you from the squad?

26:23.373 --> 26:25.667
No, I had to skip because I had some
studying to do.

26:26.251 --> 26:28.587
-That's gonna get your far with the boys.
-Mom.

26:29.212 --> 26:33.049
Oh, well, unless you're playing
for the other team now.

26:33.258 --> 26:35.552
I'm not a lesbian.

26:35.635 --> 26:38.597
-She just has no taste.
-Thank God, because your father would die.

26:38.680 --> 26:40.682
If he didn't already die in that
plane crash.

26:40.765 --> 26:43.226
-Okay, so we're... what?
-Mom! We're gonna be late!

26:43.310 --> 26:45.895
I know we are! And this isn't helping!

26:46.187 --> 26:49.065
-Do not get on the bed.
-Did you smudge her eyeliner?

26:49.149 --> 26:50.066
-Brody!
-Yes or no?

26:50.150 --> 26:50.984
-No.
-Mom!

26:51.067 --> 26:52.694
-[girl screaming]
-You know what?

26:52.777 --> 26:54.237
Brody, stop screaming!

26:54.321 --> 26:56.740
I'm gonna count. One, two...

26:59.117 --> 27:01.161
If you're gonna get messed up,
we're not gonna go.

27:01.244 --> 27:02.912
-I'm counting to three. One...
-Get off!

27:02.996 --> 27:05.081
...two… My God.

27:05.165 --> 27:06.708
Are the tassels in knots?

27:07.125 --> 27:08.793
Get out. Veronica,

27:09.377 --> 27:11.963
there's no more skipping practice,
because you know

27:12.047 --> 27:14.549
what happens when gymnasts
stop practicing, right?

27:14.633 --> 27:16.635
One day they're these cute
little firecrackers

27:16.718 --> 27:19.471
and the next day they've exploded
out of their Lycra.

27:20.930 --> 27:22.140
And it's expensive.

27:23.224 --> 27:24.142
We're leaving.

27:24.976 --> 27:25.810
Girls!

27:25.894 --> 27:27.228
-[Veronica] Fine!
-[door slams]

27:27.771 --> 27:30.190
-[Veronica's mom] Now you've slammed it?
-Yes, I slammed it.

27:30.273 --> 27:31.107
You're grounded!

27:37.447 --> 27:38.281
[Sierra] Um...

27:39.199 --> 27:40.158
Let's...

27:40.241 --> 27:41.785
Let's start with Plato.

27:51.169 --> 27:52.003
[Veronica's dad] Hey!

27:54.381 --> 27:55.757
Where you been, Kid Wonder?

27:56.049 --> 27:59.260
Tutoring. A bad student
and an even worse person.

28:00.887 --> 28:03.223
"Reeling" and "writhing," of course,
to begin with...

28:03.932 --> 28:06.267
and then the different branches
of arithmetic:

28:06.351 --> 28:08.728
ambition, distraction, uglification,
and derision.

28:09.771 --> 28:10.605
Lewis Carroll.

28:10.689 --> 28:11.523
Good.

28:11.981 --> 28:13.441
How goes the latest opus?

28:13.525 --> 28:15.151
Almost all opused.

28:16.611 --> 28:18.238
How's the poem coming for class?

28:21.741 --> 28:22.867
It's good.

28:24.244 --> 28:26.913
-When can I read it?
-When it's ready.

28:27.622 --> 28:29.999
Still iambisizing the iambic pentameter.

28:30.375 --> 28:33.253
You know the hardest part of being
a writer, still?

28:34.754 --> 28:35.630
The first read.

28:36.297 --> 28:38.383
Allowing yourself to be that vulnerable.

28:39.509 --> 28:42.345
Who makes and illustrates the way it is?

28:42.679 --> 28:45.348
The book whose words and pictures
never fade?

28:45.932 --> 28:48.268
Who writes the same edition
for every decade,

28:48.768 --> 28:53.857
plagiarizing and disguising the same
old story under the cover of change?

28:53.940 --> 28:54.858
Chapter Two,

28:55.608 --> 28:58.236
you better claim a shape or they'll name
one for you.

28:58.361 --> 29:01.781
Gay, straight, black, white,
are you the type of girl

29:01.865 --> 29:03.950
who's a friend, a fling, or a wife?

29:04.033 --> 29:06.870
Check the boxes that apply and don't think
your way outside.

29:06.953 --> 29:10.999
Replace your legs with pegs and
dig a hole to spend your remaining days

29:11.082 --> 29:13.543
fitting inside, 'cause that's when you're
living it right.

29:13.626 --> 29:16.880
At least three feet deep and
taking shallow breaths at best,

29:16.963 --> 29:20.425
because you air isn't your own,
and you're heir to your own life.

29:21.509 --> 29:23.511
[students applaud, cheer]

29:30.727 --> 29:34.606
The gauntlet has been thrown,
and the bar's set high.

29:35.106 --> 29:38.026
So for all you little Robbie Frosties,

29:38.109 --> 29:39.736
I hope this will be a challenge.

29:48.328 --> 29:49.913
I've been thinking about what you said,

29:49.996 --> 29:52.040
and I was wondering if you had
any suggestions

29:52.123 --> 29:53.875
on how to bolster my resume.

29:54.667 --> 29:56.002
What languages do you speak?

29:56.085 --> 29:58.379
French, Italian, and a little Mandarin.

29:58.505 --> 30:00.965
[counselor] Mandarin? You know
how many people speak Mandarin?

30:01.049 --> 30:02.926
About a billion Chinese.

30:03.009 --> 30:04.594
You're not getting it, Sierra.

30:04.677 --> 30:05.970
Think different.

30:07.680 --> 30:09.557
Bet Dad never gets writer's block.

30:12.852 --> 30:13.686
Okay.

30:37.210 --> 30:39.838
[Sierra] Plato believed
that physical beauty was both a form

30:39.921 --> 30:41.965
-and a sensory experience.
-[children humming]

30:42.048 --> 30:42.882
Stop!

30:43.675 --> 30:47.554
Physical beauty facilitates
platonic recollection.

30:47.637 --> 30:49.931
-Reco-what?
-Recollection.

30:54.018 --> 30:56.145
Are you sure you don't have any
real food in this house?

30:56.229 --> 30:58.731
[Veronica's mom]
No. You don't eat junk at your age.

30:59.315 --> 31:01.901
You'll make lifelong fat cells
that'll ride your hips

31:01.985 --> 31:03.528
like a cowboy rides a buckin' bronco.

31:03.611 --> 31:04.988
[Veronica's mom to girls] No, stop.

31:05.071 --> 31:06.739
-Mom.
-And then what?

31:07.657 --> 31:08.658
Okay...

31:09.409 --> 31:10.952
well, Plato was kind of a jerk,

31:11.035 --> 31:12.871
but in his more optimistic moments,

31:12.954 --> 31:15.248
he revered beauty for revealing
the mysteries of the soul.

31:15.915 --> 31:18.585
Your father was a mystery.
Until the day he died of his heart attack.

31:20.253 --> 31:21.880
Thought he died in a plane crash.

31:21.963 --> 31:24.591
Is there, like, a For Dummies version
of the For Dummies version,

31:24.674 --> 31:26.134
because I'm not understanding this.

31:26.217 --> 31:27.385
Moronica!

31:28.845 --> 31:30.930
Moronica!

31:31.848 --> 31:34.976
-So, Plato...
-The butt sex guy?

31:36.769 --> 31:37.979
-Right?
-No...

31:38.062 --> 31:39.856
I mean he was from ancient Greece,

31:39.939 --> 31:41.983
but so were Aristotle and Socrates.

31:42.275 --> 31:44.527
Wait, wait, they're not all the same guy?

31:44.611 --> 31:45.945
Moronica!

31:46.029 --> 31:47.780
-[dog barking]
-Moronica!

31:50.033 --> 31:51.868
Oh, you're not kidding?

31:51.951 --> 31:53.912
No, no, I thought we already covered--

31:53.995 --> 31:55.622
Can you stop doing that, Brody!

31:55.705 --> 31:57.332
[Veronica's mom] Girls, shh.

31:57.707 --> 31:59.584
They're studying, okay?

32:00.501 --> 32:01.669
I'll never get this.

32:03.046 --> 32:05.214
Moronica!

32:05.298 --> 32:08.760
Girls! I'm counting to five. One...

32:08.843 --> 32:10.970
two... now, upstairs.

32:12.680 --> 32:13.765
I can't.

32:24.025 --> 32:24.901
Veronica.

32:28.071 --> 32:28.947
It's pointless.

32:30.114 --> 32:31.240
I mean, they're right.

32:32.116 --> 32:33.117
I'm "Moronica."

32:38.539 --> 32:40.625
Look, you're not a moron, okay?

32:40.875 --> 32:42.961
You think of some seriously mean crap.

32:43.920 --> 32:46.673
You've gotta have something upstairs
to think of those insults.

32:51.260 --> 32:52.095
Yeah.

32:54.055 --> 32:54.889
Nevermind.

32:59.143 --> 33:00.228
So, this...

33:00.812 --> 33:02.188
this Jamey I'm dating...

33:03.398 --> 33:04.524
have you sext him yet?

33:06.192 --> 33:07.819
We can send him a nude if you want.

33:07.902 --> 33:08.820
No.

33:10.571 --> 33:11.948
No, Jamey is not like that.

33:12.031 --> 33:13.449
Everyone is like that.

33:15.994 --> 33:17.537
If you want to start off JV...

33:18.746 --> 33:20.456
-What?
-Your phone.

33:22.625 --> 33:23.793
Give me your phone.

34:04.375 --> 34:05.543
You should send those.

34:06.919 --> 34:09.130
If you're gonna pretend to be me,
be normal,

34:10.256 --> 34:11.674
or you could just die alone.

34:31.360 --> 34:32.195
[phone chimes]

34:39.702 --> 34:41.370
Oh, shit.

35:00.098 --> 35:00.932
[phone chimes]

35:05.144 --> 35:06.104
[quietly] Yeah.

35:48.229 --> 35:50.231
[phone rings]

35:56.654 --> 35:57.655
Yo!

35:59.824 --> 36:00.700
Hey!

36:11.544 --> 36:12.461
Bonsoir!

36:13.129 --> 36:16.465
Bonsoir, Mademoiselle.

36:16.549 --> 36:17.884
Good day, fair maiden.

36:18.134 --> 36:21.262
What soft light through yonder window...

36:21.345 --> 36:24.724
we're still doing old timey stuff, right?

36:24.974 --> 36:26.517
Yeah, totally.

36:27.727 --> 36:30.563
I'm just super-glad that you picked up

36:30.646 --> 36:31.564
because if you hadn't,

36:31.647 --> 36:33.524
then I would have had to, like,

36:33.608 --> 36:35.026
come up with some sort of

36:35.109 --> 36:37.486
hilarious voicemail to impress you,

36:37.570 --> 36:40.990
and that would have been
super-terrible for both of us, you know?

36:41.073 --> 36:44.702
No, don't you hate that pressure?

36:45.494 --> 36:48.873
It's kinda… it's kinda interesting.
Your voice sounds different

36:49.123 --> 36:50.666
than I remember it.

36:51.667 --> 36:52.543
Oh, yeah.

36:52.627 --> 36:56.005
I have a cold, so it's kinda mannish.

36:56.088 --> 36:57.882
Oh, sorry.

36:59.091 --> 37:01.594
That's sucks, though, 'cause I
kinda like it, you know.

37:01.886 --> 37:03.888
Maybe you should just get sick more often

37:03.971 --> 37:05.223
and then I'll be happy.

37:05.514 --> 37:08.059
Oh, okay, because you're what,
super into dudes?

37:08.142 --> 37:10.144
Whoa, whoa. [laughs]

37:10.228 --> 37:12.563
That's just--
I mean, we are the superior sex.

37:12.688 --> 37:14.148
Oh, yeah.

37:14.232 --> 37:18.486
No, your voice, it's not loud
or anything,

37:18.569 --> 37:20.988
it's like more fuller...

37:22.156 --> 37:23.157
maybe.

37:23.241 --> 37:25.159
You calling my voice fat right now?

37:25.243 --> 37:28.579
-No, no...
-Is that what's happening?

37:28.788 --> 37:30.748
Oh, my God! No, no, no.

37:30.831 --> 37:34.794
I would never do that because I was,
like, a super-fat baby.

37:36.629 --> 37:39.507
-Why would I... I have no idea why?
-You were a fat baby?

37:39.882 --> 37:41.968
Yeah, I was like the Michelin man.

37:42.760 --> 37:46.180
No, don't stop. I like hearing about
what's wrong with you.

37:46.597 --> 37:49.225
No, I'm sorry. That was my only flaw.

37:49.308 --> 37:50.726
I would totally tell you more.

37:50.810 --> 37:53.354
That was my one and only flaw,

37:53.437 --> 37:56.983
and you somehow got it out of me,
so thank you very much for that.

37:57.525 --> 37:59.527
Actually, no, I lied.

37:59.610 --> 38:01.946
I totally just lied to you.
I do have one more,

38:02.238 --> 38:06.951
and it's that I have these
glow in the dark stickers

38:07.034 --> 38:09.620
on my ceiling that have been there
for the past ten years.

38:10.079 --> 38:12.456
But besides that, I'm perfect, basically.

38:12.540 --> 38:13.958
What about you?

38:14.417 --> 38:17.753
You got any dark secrets I should
know about?

38:20.881 --> 38:24.302
None immediately come to mind.

38:25.386 --> 38:28.180
What about, like, secret talents?

38:29.348 --> 38:31.392
-Sandwiches?
-I love sandwiches.

38:31.892 --> 38:33.894
What's your favorite movie?

38:34.812 --> 38:36.147
Probably Die Hard.

38:36.272 --> 38:37.773
-Really?
-No, that's a complete lie.

38:37.857 --> 38:39.108
Just trying to be manly for you.

38:41.360 --> 38:44.363
-What kinda animal would you be?
-[Jamey] I think I'd be a bear,

38:44.447 --> 38:49.035
because they're like, super-cuddly
but also really bad-ass,

38:49.160 --> 38:51.037
you know, double-sided like that.

38:52.496 --> 38:54.165
So what's your double side, then?

38:54.248 --> 38:55.875
Are you more than just a hot jock?

38:55.958 --> 38:57.126
Oh, you think I'm hot?

38:57.877 --> 38:58.753
No.

38:59.503 --> 39:03.966
To answer your question, I don't really
consider myself a jock.

39:05.134 --> 39:07.803
I mean, yeah, I like football,

39:07.887 --> 39:10.806
but between you and me, I don't even like
most of the guys on my team.

39:10.890 --> 39:15.311
I love football 'cause every game
is like a story.

39:16.729 --> 39:19.732
For a few hours there are villains
and there are heroes.

39:19.815 --> 39:23.736
Every pass is a triumph,
every tackle is a tragedy.

39:23.819 --> 39:27.198
You're all hurtling downfield at this
one epic goal

39:27.281 --> 39:30.701
and every second matters.
It's electric, you know.

39:30.868 --> 39:33.245
It's like poetry...

39:34.121 --> 39:35.373
to me, at least

39:38.125 --> 39:40.336
I can't go telling
the rest of the team that.

39:41.504 --> 39:42.671
They'd be freaking out.

39:42.755 --> 39:46.300
I'm the quarterback,
so I got to keep their respect.

39:50.513 --> 39:53.015
