58:15.617 --> 58:16.993
You look so cold right now.

58:17.076 --> 58:18.661
I'm going to get you a jacket, okay.

58:25.168 --> 58:26.002
[door closes]

58:27.754 --> 58:29.172
[Jamey] Here you go.

58:31.174 --> 58:32.008
Thanks.

58:35.762 --> 58:36.679
You like stars?

58:39.224 --> 58:40.099
[Veronica] Yeah.

58:40.225 --> 58:42.435
[Jamey] I'm kind of obsessed
with astronomy.

58:43.311 --> 58:45.813
-[Veronica] Nerd. Why?
-Nerd?

58:47.232 --> 58:49.776
[Jamey] Well, because...

58:50.235 --> 58:51.694
we look at them from down here

58:51.778 --> 58:53.821
-and they look so beautiful and shiny.
-[phone buzzes]

58:55.031 --> 58:57.075
They're actually just made up of hydrogen,

58:57.450 --> 58:59.994
which means that they're just
massive balls of gas

59:00.078 --> 59:01.996
floating through space and I think
it's trippy.

59:05.917 --> 59:07.794
Change of perspective, you know.

59:09.712 --> 59:11.881
I wonder if a star knows that it shuns.

59:13.341 --> 59:14.300
Shines.

59:17.220 --> 59:20.557
-If a star knows that it shines.
-Yeah, I never thought of that.

59:24.936 --> 59:26.896
Do you know what you wanna be
when you grow up?

59:37.865 --> 59:39.200
It was a stupid question.

59:47.584 --> 59:48.751
Should be a singer.

59:49.919 --> 59:51.004
I should be a singer?

59:51.921 --> 59:54.716
-Oh, no, not you.
-Oh, you should be a singer?

59:54.841 --> 59:57.176
-No, no, no, not me!
-You should sing for me.

59:57.260 --> 59:59.887
-I can't sing. It was obviously a joke.
-Wait, alright, hold on.

1:00:00.013 --> 1:00:02.140
You want to be a singer, but you don't
know how to sing.

1:00:02.724 --> 1:00:04.225
-It was a joke?
-It was a joke.

1:00:04.309 --> 1:00:05.518
[Veronica laughs]

1:00:05.602 --> 1:00:06.436
[dryly] Ah, ha, ha.

1:00:08.730 --> 1:00:11.232
I haven't really thought about life
after high school,

1:00:11.316 --> 1:00:12.358
I've got to be honest.

1:00:13.526 --> 1:00:14.485
Until I met Sierra.

1:00:16.029 --> 1:00:18.406
I literally just met a Sierra.

1:00:18.489 --> 1:00:19.616
-Really?
-Yeah.

1:00:20.950 --> 1:00:22.744
You'd really like my Sierra.

1:00:23.244 --> 1:00:25.830
Not at first. You'd think she was like,
a loser, you know.

1:00:25.913 --> 1:00:27.540
Well, so are we, right?

1:00:28.333 --> 1:00:30.710
Yeah, sure I'm a quarterback

1:00:30.793 --> 1:00:32.086
and you're a cheerleader, but...

1:00:33.212 --> 1:00:34.547
under all that, you are...

1:00:35.757 --> 1:00:36.674
so different.

1:00:44.515 --> 1:00:46.017
[gasps] Oh, my God!

1:00:46.100 --> 1:00:47.602
-What, are you okay?
-Yes.

1:00:47.685 --> 1:00:49.437
-What...
-Yes, I...

1:00:50.355 --> 1:00:53.024
-I got really excited.
-So you just jumped?

1:00:53.107 --> 1:00:53.983
Yes.

1:00:54.776 --> 1:00:57.987
Is that gonna happen every time
I try to kiss you, you're gonna jump?

1:00:59.238 --> 1:01:00.615
Would you close your eyes?

1:01:01.449 --> 1:01:03.493
Because I have really big pores.

1:01:04.285 --> 1:01:06.621
-So can you close your eyes?
-I have big pores.

1:01:06.788 --> 1:01:08.956
-Can you close them?
-You want me to close my eyes,

1:01:09.040 --> 1:01:11.834
-my eyes are closed.
-Yes. And keep them closed.

1:01:11.918 --> 1:01:15.254
My eyes are gonna stay closed
until you give me other orders.

1:01:16.923 --> 1:01:17.757
What are you doing?

1:01:17.840 --> 1:01:19.342
Are you, like, abandoning me?

1:01:19.425 --> 1:01:20.718
I'm right here.

1:01:22.136 --> 1:01:23.262
Sorry.

1:01:24.389 --> 1:01:26.391
[both silently mouthing]

1:01:28.643 --> 1:01:29.477
[chuckles]

1:01:32.939 --> 1:01:34.524
Well, it was worth the wait.

1:01:36.025 --> 1:01:38.027
It's weird, we talked so much on the phone

1:01:38.111 --> 1:01:42.115
it actually feels, like, more normal
when I can't see you.

1:02:03.177 --> 1:02:05.304
Keep them closed! I said keep them closed.

1:02:05.888 --> 1:02:07.306
Okay, they are closed.

1:02:07.598 --> 1:02:09.475
Veronica, this is ridiculous.

1:02:09.559 --> 1:02:11.102
Veronica, I just want to see you.

1:02:11.185 --> 1:02:12.603
Well, see me now.

1:02:14.856 --> 1:02:17.400
You wanted to see me,
now you're not even looking.

1:02:17.525 --> 1:02:21.779
-Well, yeah, but I thought I saw some...
-What, you saw... what?

1:02:23.740 --> 1:02:25.783
You're acting so weird right now.

1:02:28.202 --> 1:02:30.997
[Jamey] Am I gonna have to go through that
every time I try to kiss you?

1:02:31.664 --> 1:02:34.917
If you're crazy, that's just something
that I need to know about

1:02:35.042 --> 1:02:37.170
-before I take you on a second date.
-I'll let you know.

1:02:44.719 --> 1:02:46.095
[Sierra] It was incredible.

1:02:48.055 --> 1:02:50.141
The kind of kiss you read about in books,

1:02:50.224 --> 1:02:51.893
but never believe could happen.

1:02:53.728 --> 1:02:54.562
Mm-hmm.

1:02:56.355 --> 1:02:59.108
You wanna hang out and go over
our debate platform?

1:03:00.026 --> 1:03:00.860
Yeah, maybe.

1:03:00.943 --> 1:03:03.362
I'm just kind of swamped
with college stuff right now.

1:03:04.363 --> 1:03:05.615
Yeah, yeah.

1:03:09.702 --> 1:03:10.536
Sorry.

1:03:12.288 --> 1:03:13.790
Why do people do this to themselves?

1:03:13.998 --> 1:03:15.249
Because it looks pretty.

1:03:15.750 --> 1:03:17.126
And they're almost even.

1:03:19.504 --> 1:03:20.922
Your mom's really pretty.

1:03:21.255 --> 1:03:23.007
You should see her prom pictures.

1:03:23.633 --> 1:03:26.385
The night of, or the morning after?

1:03:26.511 --> 1:03:30.014
-No, I do not need to think about that.
-Sorry. I'm sorry.

1:03:32.934 --> 1:03:34.143
Can I ask you something?

1:03:34.227 --> 1:03:36.479
I'm not gonna les out with you
and Jamie.

1:03:37.647 --> 1:03:39.524
-No, no.
-I only do that at parties.

1:03:40.066 --> 1:03:41.818
Why does everybody think I'm a lesbian?

1:03:43.069 --> 1:03:44.070
No, I...

1:03:44.821 --> 1:03:48.908
I wanted to ask, what's up with your mom?

1:03:50.159 --> 1:03:51.953
What-- What happened to your dad?

1:03:52.995 --> 1:03:53.913
He...

1:03:55.039 --> 1:03:57.250
he left her for a 22-year-old.

1:03:57.959 --> 1:04:02.547
And left us with all this crap
and furniture and...

1:04:03.130 --> 1:04:05.383
no way to pay for our old house, and...

1:04:06.342 --> 1:04:09.220
she's just been weird about this
whole fading youth stuff ever since.

1:04:12.306 --> 1:04:13.182
I'm sorry.

1:04:15.560 --> 1:04:16.978
I should probably get ready.

1:04:18.813 --> 1:04:19.939
I'm going to a party.

1:04:21.732 --> 1:04:22.775
Do you want to come?

1:04:24.485 --> 1:04:26.195
Like, together?

1:04:26.988 --> 1:04:27.864
In public?

1:04:29.532 --> 1:04:30.449
Yeah.

1:04:34.662 --> 1:04:35.496
Sierra.

1:04:35.913 --> 1:04:37.957
You are so tense right now.

1:04:38.082 --> 1:04:40.001
-Smile.
-Calm down.

1:04:40.084 --> 1:04:41.669
-It's a party.
-I know.

1:04:42.044 --> 1:04:44.046
-That's what's so terrifying.
-No!

1:04:44.714 --> 1:04:46.716
[overlapping chatter]

1:04:55.182 --> 1:04:57.351
-[Veronica] Hey, how's it going?
-Hey!

1:05:02.315 --> 1:05:03.274
Hey, Ronnie.

1:05:03.816 --> 1:05:05.026
I thought you were sick.

1:05:05.651 --> 1:05:08.029
Who's ready to get this bitch started?
Let's go!

1:05:08.321 --> 1:05:10.072
Sorry about that, ladies,
sorry about that.

1:05:11.866 --> 1:05:13.492
I need to talk to you... now.

1:05:14.368 --> 1:05:15.244
Sure.

1:05:15.703 --> 1:05:17.246
Like, alone, outside.

1:05:19.040 --> 1:05:20.625
Okay. Sure, let's go.

1:05:23.044 --> 1:05:24.128
I'll be right back.

1:05:48.486 --> 1:05:50.071
[phone chimes]

1:05:57.286 --> 1:05:58.579
You probably deserved it.

1:05:58.663 --> 1:06:00.539
Probably ditched your best friend too.

1:06:00.873 --> 1:06:01.749
[weight thuds]

1:06:02.917 --> 1:06:04.961
So what's the real story?

1:06:05.252 --> 1:06:07.088
[boy speaking Mandarin]

1:06:07.171 --> 1:06:08.631
Veronica... [speaking in Mandarin]

1:06:09.090 --> 1:06:11.050
Wow, everybody does speak Mandarin.

1:06:11.133 --> 1:06:13.761
-Come on wreck, keg stand, now. Let's go!
-What?

1:06:13.844 --> 1:06:15.054
You're gonna love it.

1:06:15.137 --> 1:06:16.764
[girl] You're such a drama queen now.

1:06:18.140 --> 1:06:19.266
She's not that bad.

1:06:19.892 --> 1:06:20.726
She's--

1:06:20.810 --> 1:06:22.603
Oh, my God! Oh, my God!

1:06:23.896 --> 1:06:25.439
She's actually kinda cool.

1:06:26.148 --> 1:06:27.817
Like, a totally unfortunate way.

1:06:28.067 --> 1:06:30.945
If you wanna commit social suicide, fine,

1:06:31.112 --> 1:06:33.280
but Sierra Burgess is a loser.

1:06:33.823 --> 1:06:34.991
Remember?

1:06:35.074 --> 1:06:37.493
Only losers hang out with losers.

1:06:42.581 --> 1:06:43.499
Mackenzie, wait.

1:06:43.582 --> 1:06:45.793
Yo, everyone in here! Everyone in here!

1:06:46.085 --> 1:06:47.962
[boys chanting] Chug, chug! Chug, chug!

1:06:48.045 --> 1:06:50.423
[boy] Come on, everybody
gather around! Watch this!

1:06:52.258 --> 1:06:54.885
Chug, chug! Chug, chug!

1:07:10.776 --> 1:07:11.610
[burps]

1:07:12.695 --> 1:07:13.612
Whoo!

1:07:18.868 --> 1:07:20.244
You tamed the beast!

1:07:20.453 --> 1:07:21.287
My turn.

1:07:21.454 --> 1:07:23.748
Come on, let's go. Get me up here.

1:07:26.125 --> 1:07:28.085
Chug, chug! Chug, chug!

1:07:30.671 --> 1:07:33.090
[boy] I told Veronica she's dumb
to make her insecure.

1:07:33.674 --> 1:07:36.052
I guarantee she puts out tonight.

1:07:38.429 --> 1:07:39.805
You're the master.

1:07:39.930 --> 1:07:41.307
I bow down to you, sir.

1:07:47.688 --> 1:07:48.522
Hi.

1:07:49.106 --> 1:07:50.483
I love your poodle.

1:07:53.152 --> 1:07:54.653
That's so adorable.

1:07:59.366 --> 1:08:00.326
Dick!

1:08:20.888 --> 1:08:22.181
Oh, my God! Jesus!

1:08:23.599 --> 1:08:24.475
Spence?

1:08:26.477 --> 1:08:27.728
What are you doing here?

1:08:29.313 --> 1:08:31.398
I saw your post and I had to see you.

1:08:32.608 --> 1:08:33.651
My Hamlet video?

1:08:34.068 --> 1:08:37.321
What? No, the one about this party.

1:08:40.116 --> 1:08:41.242
Do you wanna get out of here?

1:08:42.118 --> 1:08:44.912
This place is, like, crawling with dudes.

1:08:44.995 --> 1:08:46.705
I can't just ditch my friend.

1:08:49.125 --> 1:08:50.000
Come on.

1:08:52.878 --> 1:08:53.838
Go where?

1:08:53.921 --> 1:08:55.881
Babe, just for a second.

1:08:56.549 --> 1:08:57.383
Come on.

1:08:59.218 --> 1:09:00.219
We need to talk.

1:09:01.428 --> 1:09:02.346
In my car.

1:09:38.257 --> 1:09:39.300
Pick up.

1:09:40.259 --> 1:09:41.427
Pick up, Veronica.

1:09:44.763 --> 1:09:47.016
Plato believed that physical beauty...

1:09:48.225 --> 1:09:51.770
could be in the form of,
you know, sensory experience and...

1:09:53.272 --> 1:09:55.399
I'm enjoying this sensory experience.

1:10:06.327 --> 1:10:07.453
What? Wait.

1:10:19.506 --> 1:10:20.341
Frick!

1:11:00.673 --> 1:11:01.799
[phone buzzes]

1:11:16.897 --> 1:11:18.899
[phone ringing]

1:11:20.276 --> 1:11:21.110
Hello?

1:11:23.904 --> 1:11:24.738
Hello?

1:11:26.991 --> 1:11:27.992
Are you there?

1:11:29.368 --> 1:11:30.744
I really like you.

1:11:36.166 --> 1:11:37.251
I...

1:11:37.918 --> 1:11:39.920
I really, really like you.

1:11:43.424 --> 1:11:46.302
Because you're so good. You're so good.

1:11:48.429 --> 1:11:49.596
You don't lie.

1:11:51.140 --> 1:11:52.766
You don't speak Chinese.

1:11:53.017 --> 1:11:54.518
-and you don't--
-Wait, wait.

1:11:55.102 --> 1:11:56.729
Are you drunk right now?

1:11:58.355 --> 1:11:59.940
Do you think you could like me?

1:12:02.568 --> 1:12:03.485
Like...

1:12:03.986 --> 1:12:05.946
really like me, like, not for my...

1:12:06.947 --> 1:12:09.616
my stupid looks, or because I'm deaf--

1:12:09.700 --> 1:12:12.745
-and because I...
-Wait, wait. Wait.

1:12:12.995 --> 1:12:14.371
What are you talking about?

1:12:14.455 --> 1:12:16.165
I need to tell you something,

1:12:16.790 --> 1:12:18.417
and you're gonna hate me.

1:12:18.876 --> 1:12:19.710
I...

1:12:20.836 --> 1:12:21.879
I doubt that.

1:12:22.129 --> 1:12:24.006
I don't think I could ever hate you.

1:12:24.089 --> 1:12:25.466
No matter what you tell me.

1:12:25.799 --> 1:12:26.967
I think you're gonna.

1:12:31.513 --> 1:12:33.057
What, is it really that bad?

1:12:41.315 --> 1:12:42.149
[snores]

1:12:58.665 --> 1:12:59.875
Goodnight.

1:13:04.296 --> 1:13:06.507
[Sierra's mom]
Honey, do you know what kind of kids

1:13:06.590 --> 1:13:08.509
go to a party and get drunk?

1:13:09.676 --> 1:13:11.428
Kids with low self-esteem.

1:13:12.054 --> 1:13:14.431
Sierra, do you have low self-esteem?

1:13:15.015 --> 1:13:15.933
Mom.

1:13:16.225 --> 1:13:20.229
I thought we taught you R-E-S-P-E-C-T.

1:13:20.521 --> 1:13:22.898
-Rein in...
-Every Self-doubt,

1:13:22.981 --> 1:13:25.359
Peer Expectation and Competitive Thought.

1:13:25.442 --> 1:13:27.277
-Yes, Mom. I know, okay?
-Okay.

1:13:27.361 --> 1:13:29.696
Wait a minute. Before you try
to argue your way out of this,

1:13:29.780 --> 1:13:32.449
which we all know you can do
with exceptional talent,

1:13:32.533 --> 1:13:33.367
you're grounded.

1:13:34.076 --> 1:13:35.702
-What?
-You're grounded.

1:13:35.869 --> 1:13:36.870
-Honey, we...
-Dad!

1:13:36.954 --> 1:13:39.748
-...talked about this.
-No, Jules, you talked about it.

1:13:39.998 --> 1:13:41.959
It was some motto
that spelled out "free to fly,"

1:13:42.042 --> 1:13:43.293
but this is my house too,

1:13:43.377 --> 1:13:45.421
where there are actions and consequences,

1:13:45.504 --> 1:13:48.132
and this little drunk birdie
needs her wings clipped.

1:13:49.091 --> 1:13:51.927
It is not appropriate to ground her.

1:13:52.511 --> 1:13:54.179
-Why not?
-Well, because!

1:13:54.596 --> 1:13:55.848
What has gotten into her?

1:13:56.807 --> 1:13:58.058
"We hop in the car.

1:13:58.434 --> 1:13:59.643
It's a super fast ride."

1:14:00.644 --> 1:14:03.981
"We dance on the bar
and have a sweet time."

1:14:04.356 --> 1:14:06.358
[scattered applause]

1:14:07.526 --> 1:14:09.945
[Ms. T] Inspired, Chrissy.
You could co-write for Kesha.

1:14:11.613 --> 1:14:12.573
And now,

1:14:12.781 --> 1:14:17.202
last but not least, our resident progeny
of literary greatness,

1:14:17.286 --> 1:14:18.662
Sierra Burgess.

1:14:21.790 --> 1:14:23.000
Sierra!

1:14:27.588 --> 1:14:28.547
I forgot.

1:14:28.839 --> 1:14:30.299
What do you mean you forgot?

1:14:31.049 --> 1:14:33.093
Are you trying to prove a point?

1:14:34.344 --> 1:14:35.220
I forgot.

1:14:35.929 --> 1:14:37.264
I'm sorry, there's just...

1:14:37.723 --> 1:14:39.475
so much has been going on lately

1:14:39.558 --> 1:14:40.893
and it slipped my mind.

1:14:41.518 --> 1:14:43.604
Well, you know this is going to cost you.

1:14:43.937 --> 1:14:46.565
-And you still have to do the assignment.
-[bell rings]

1:14:46.648 --> 1:14:49.026
I passed out, and I have no idea
if I told the truth.

1:14:49.109 --> 1:14:51.361
By the time Ronnie called me back,
she'd already done it.

1:14:51.445 --> 1:14:53.197
I didn't have the heart to tell her
the truth.

1:14:54.239 --> 1:14:56.492
But I thought y'all
wasn't going out last night.

1:14:56.575 --> 1:14:58.327
You told me you wasn't going out.

1:14:58.410 --> 1:15:00.204
-That's why we couldn't hang out.
-Okay, well--

1:15:01.330 --> 1:15:03.248
Hey, hey. What's wrong?

1:15:03.332 --> 1:15:05.334
I just need a hug. I just--

1:15:06.126 --> 1:15:08.754
-Ronnie, what happened? Are you okay?
-He dumped me.

1:15:08.837 --> 1:15:10.839
Spence, he dumped me again.

1:15:12.841 --> 1:15:14.718
-Over DM.
-God.

1:15:14.801 --> 1:15:16.553
-I know.
-Ronnie.

1:15:17.137 --> 1:15:18.889
-Can we talk?
-Yeah.

1:15:18.972 --> 1:15:21.808
-What the shit?
-Not now, Dan. Okay?

1:15:21.892 --> 1:15:22.851
I-- Let's go.

1:15:31.235 --> 1:15:32.486
Some people just suck.

1:15:32.569 --> 1:15:34.947
And if he doesn't like you for you,
then screw him anyway.

1:15:35.030 --> 1:15:37.491
This would never have happened
if I dated someone like Jamey.

1:15:38.450 --> 1:15:40.160
He's one of the good ones. He's...

1:15:40.410 --> 1:15:41.495
he's hot and...

1:15:41.995 --> 1:15:44.706
-weird, smart, and--
-Do you like him?

1:15:46.625 --> 1:15:47.501
No!

1:15:53.715 --> 1:15:54.967
[phone buzzes]

1:15:59.471 --> 1:16:00.305
Hey.

1:16:00.472 --> 1:16:03.183
[Sierra] Hey, so about last night.

1:16:04.643 --> 1:16:06.603
Did I say something weird?

1:16:06.812 --> 1:16:08.855
Oh, you mean while you were
white-girl wasted?

1:16:09.231 --> 1:16:11.608
Yeah, I think weird would be
an understatement.

1:16:11.692 --> 1:16:12.901
What did I tell you?

1:16:14.069 --> 1:16:15.112
What do you think...

1:16:15.404 --> 1:16:16.280
that you told me?

1:16:16.363 --> 1:16:18.740
What do you think I think you think
I told you?

1:16:19.616 --> 1:16:23.120
What, are you, like, afraid to tell me
that you like me or something?

1:16:24.121 --> 1:16:25.122
No!

1:16:27.082 --> 1:16:27.916
No?

1:16:28.292 --> 1:16:32.588
No, I mean, yeah, no. I don't know.

1:16:33.046 --> 1:16:35.424
Let's just not say it
over the phone, okay?

1:16:35.924 --> 1:16:37.134
Not like this.

1:16:37.467 --> 1:16:41.221
Okay. Well, then this silence...

